items: Sir Charles Beauclair , first a Younger Brother , marri'd by his Friends , to a Rich ill-favour'd Widow , afterwards Master of a great Estate , and in Love with Bellinda .
Beaumont an honest Country Gentleman , Friend to Sir Francis : and Lover of Arabella .
Spendall a Sharper ; and hanger on to Sir Charles .
Lywell , a Rake , Companion to Spendal .
Cheatall , a very foolish Fellow ; Brother to the Lady Beauclair .
Gentil , his Man ; an Ingenious Fellow .
Mr. Flywife , alias Allen , a Merchant .
Bellinda , alias Mariamne , Daughter to the Lord Belmour .
Mrs. Beauclair , Niece to Sir Charles .
Arabella , a young Lady , left to the Care of Cheatall's Father .
Lady Beauclair , an ill bred Woman .
Peggy , her Daughter , of the same Stamp .
Mrs. Flywife , kept by Flywife , and going by his Name .
